## Calendar Event Rules

Create one calendar event section after the Owner Closeout Report.

- Create only one calendar event.
- Do not create separate events for individual items.
- Title must be: Owner Command Center
- Event is for tomorrow morning.
- Use 8:00 AM to 9:00 AM by default.
- If tomorrow is Monday, Thursday, or Friday, use 9:00 AM to 10:00 AM.
- Use the Current Date provided in the input to calculate tomorrow’s actual date.
- Do not guess the current date.
- Do not use example dates, prior outputs, or test data.
- Do not use timezone names like EST, EDT, Eastern, or America/New_York.
- Do not write “Tomorrow at” in Start Date & Time or End Date & Time.
- Use this date/time format exactly:
MM/DD/YYYY h:mm AM/PM

Calendar Description should include the useful action information from the closeout report:
- Top 3 Priorities
- Client Items
- Business / Admin Tasks
- Reminders / Follow-Ups
- Suggested Starting Point

Do not include Ideas / Future Consideration unless High priority, due tomorrow, or clearly time-sensitive.
Do not include Needs Cleanup unless the unclear item blocks tomorrow’s work.

---

## Fallback Output

If no open items are provided, return exactly:

Owner Closeout Report

No open command center items found for today.
Tomorrow’s starting point is clear unless new items were captured outside this system.
